    "54702890": {
      "title": "Colony PCR-Single strand conformation polymorphism for the detection of Ralstonia solanacearum in tomato",
      "abstract": "In India bacterial wilt caused by Ralstonia solanacearum is the most destructive disease of vegetable plants. In an attempt to identify R. solanacearum by direct colony Polymerase Chain Reaction-Single Strand Confirmation Polymorphism (PCR-SSCP) technique. R. solanacearum was isolated and confirmed by biochem., physiol., hypersensitivity and pathogenicity tests. In addn., 16S rRNA and specific PCR primers were used to detect the pathogen in infected plant material/soil sample. In order to perform a DNA-based diagnostic test, availability of a rapid and easy-to-perform DNA extn. protocol is essential. In the present study we evaluated colony PCR-SSCP as the easiest way to amplify the target DNA and PCR-SSCP is a simple and powerful technique for identifying sequence changes in amplified DNA. We have developed colony PCR-SSCP technique to identify phytopathogenic bacteria by the PCR product without DNA isolation was denatured and sepd. on a non-denaturing polyacrylamide gel. SSCP banding patterns were detected by silver staining of nucleic acids and compared with the other phytopathogenic bacteria. The application of colony PCR-SSCP technique for the detection and diagnosis of R. solanacearum is discussed in the present paper. [on SciFinder(R)]"
    }
  }
}